Package com.mhealthatlas.enterpriseapps.command

Interface IAndroidAppCommandService

All Known Implementing Classes:
AndroidAppCommandService
public interface IAndroidAppCommandService
Contains handler methods for events created by the Application service.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void handleAndroidAppAdded​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode appData)
    Handels a "android_application_added" event.
    Therefor the event payload is mapped to an AppEventDto and transformed in a AndroidApp and AndroidAppVersion entity.
    void handleAndroidAppChanged​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode appData)
    Handels a "android_application_changed" event.
    Therefor the event payload is mapped to an AppEventDto and transformed in a AndroidApp entity.

  • Method Details

    • handleAndroidAppAdded

      void handleAndroidAppAdded​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode appData) throws com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException
      Handels a "android_application_added" event.
      Therefor the event payload is mapped to an AppEventDto and transformed in a AndroidApp and AndroidAppVersion entity. Then the entities are saved to store the data changes in the database.
      Parameters:
      appData - the event application data
      Throws:
      com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException - if the appData cannot be converted to a AppEventDto.

    • handleAndroidAppDeleted

      void handleAndroidAppDeleted​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode appData) throws com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException
      Handels a "android_application_version_deleted" event.
      Therefor the event payload is mapped to an AppIdEventDto. Then the android application is deleted using the AppIdEventDto object.
      Parameters:
      appData - the event application data
      Throws:
      com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException - if the appData cannot be converted to a AppIdEventDto.

    • handleAndroidAppRelationChanged

      void handleAndroidAppRelationChanged​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode appData) throws com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException
      Handels a "android_application_relation_changed" event.
      Therefor the event payload is mapped to an AppRelationEventDto. Then the relation is created and stored in the database.
      Parameters:
      appData - the event application data
      Throws:
      com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException - if the appData cannot be converted to a AppRelationEventDto.

    • handleAndroidAppRelationRemoved
